⚙️ How to Run
Requirements
Python 3.x installed on your computer
Tkinter (comes built-in with Python)
Steps
Clone the repository
```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/student-academic-management-system.git
   ```
Navigate into the project folder
```bash
   cd student-academic-management-system
   ```
Run the application
```bash
   python student_academic_management_system.py
   ```
> No additional installations are required. All libraries used are part of Python's standard library.
---
🔑 How to Use
First Time Setup
Run the application
Click Admin Signup and create the first Admin account
The first Admin is automatically approved and can log in immediately
Adding Users
Log in as Admin
Other users (Teachers, Students, Principals) sign up through the login screen
Admin approves or rejects accounts from the Pending Approvals panel
Adding Grades (Teacher)
Log in as Teacher
Click Add/Update Student Grades
Enter the student's username, subject, and score (0–100)
Viewing Results (Student)
Log in as Student
Click View My Results to see grades, letter grades, and average
Click Print My Results to save a result sheet as a text file
